## specs
- label: app install spec documents missing Harbor CLI detection and official installer flow
  command: test -f scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'official installer' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'Windows host prerequisite' scripts/specs/app-install.md
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: app install spec covers a zero-to-running flow where a user can install the Harbor App, install Harbor CLI and platform dependencies, configure Open WebUI plus llama.cpp, verify inference with a small model, and open Open WebUI from a clean machine
  command: rg -q 'Zero-to-Running Scope' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'harbor up --no-defaults llamacpp webui' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'Open WebUI' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'inference' scripts/specs/app-install.md
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: app install spec requires install.sh and install.ps1 to own platform prerequisite installation, conditional branching, and Windows interop while the app orchestrates setup state
  command: rg -q 'install.sh' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'install.ps1' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'platform conditionals' scripts/specs/app-install.md
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: app install spec defines zero-to-running readiness as Open WebUI plus llama.cpp running and completing inference with a small model
  command: rg -q 'Open WebUI' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'llama.cpp' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'small model' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'inference' scripts/specs/app-install.md
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: app install spec pins the first-run llama.cpp smoke model to unsloth/Qwen3.5-0.8B-GGUF Q4_K_M unless replaced by a verified Harbor-owned pointer
  command: rg -q 'unsloth/Qwen3.5-0.8B-GGUF' scripts/specs/app-install.md && rg -q 'Qwen3.5-0.8B-Q4_K_M.gguf' scripts/specs/app-install.md
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows WSL distro lookup caches only successful distro names so transient setup-state misses cannot pin later app commands to the default WSL distro
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src/harborCommand.ts","utf8"); if (!src.includes("cachedWindowsWslDistro = distro")) process.exit(1); if (src.includes("cachedWindowsWslDistro = null")) process.exit(1); if (!/if \(distro\) \{\s*cachedWindowsWslDistro = distro;\s*\}/s.test(src)) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App full setup releases the setup-active lock before returning final detection so a successful first-run install can return ready instead of a stale running stage
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); const start=src.indexOf("fn start_harbor_setup_inner"); const end=src.indexOf("pub fn run_setup_smoke", start); const body=src.slice(start,end); const guard=body.indexOf("let guard = acquire_setup_lock(state)?"); const drop=body.indexOf("drop(guard)"); const detect=body.indexOf("Ok(detect_harbor_setup_inner(state))"); if (guard < 0 || drop < guard || detect < drop) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup detection preserves the current setup stage while setup is active so redetect or remount cannot reset an in-progress setup screen to checking-platform
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!src.includes("current_stage: Arc<Mutex<Option<String>>>") || !src.includes("fn set_current_stage") || !src.includes("fn current_setup_stage")) process.exit(1); const detectStart=src.indexOf("pub fn detect_harbor_setup"); const detectEnd=src.indexOf("#[tauri::command]", detectStart + 1); const detect=src.slice(detectStart, detectEnd); if (!/if running\s*\{[\s\S]*detail\.status = current_setup_stage\(&state\);[\s\S]*return detail;/.test(detect)) process.exit(1); const runStart=src.indexOf("fn run_logged("); const runEnd=src.indexOf("fn run_logged_shell", runStart); const run=src.slice(runStart, runEnd); if (!run.includes("set_current_stage(state, stage)") || !run.includes("reader_current_stage")) process.exit(1); const lineStart=src.indexOf("fn emit_process_line"); const lineEnd=src.indexOf("fn emit_process_chunk", lineStart); const line=src.slice(lineStart,lineEnd); if (!line.includes("current_stage_state") || !line.includes("Some(marker.clone())")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App release packaging uses a pinned Bun version instead of latest so macOS and Windows app builds are reproducible across runner image updates
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync(".github/workflows/app-release.yml","utf8"); if (!src.includes("oven-sh/setup-bun@v2")) process.exit(1); if (!/bun-version:\s*1\.3\.9/.test(src)) process.exit(1); if (/bun-version:\s*latest/.test(src)) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Bun lock resolves the same Vite and Tauri frontend build tool versions as package-lock so release packaging does not run stale cross-platform build tooling
  command: cd app && bun pm ls | rg -q 'vite@5\.4\.21' && bun pm ls | rg -q '@vitejs/plugin-react@4\.7\.0' && bun pm ls | rg -q '@tauri-apps/cli@2\.11\.2'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App disables DaisyUI build logs so release packaging does not emit wide Unicode output from Tailwind generation
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/tailwind.config.js","utf8"); if (!/logs:\s*false/.test(src) || /logs:\s*true/.test(src)) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App service docs raw-import only text documentation files so release builds do not parse binary docs assets as raw modules
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src/service/ServiceDocs.tsx","utf8"); if (!src.includes("import.meta.glob(\"/src/docs/*.{md,yml,yaml}\"") || src.includes("import.meta.glob(\"/src/docs/*\"")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App exposes a native setup smoke mode that runs the same full Tauri setup backend and writes a JSON result for host validation
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const lib=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/lib.rs","utf8"); const setup=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!lib.includes("HARBOR_APP_SETUP_SMOKE") || !lib.includes("spawn_setup_smoke")) process.exit(1); if (!setup.includes("run_setup_smoke") || !setup.includes("HARBOR_APP_SETUP_SMOKE_OUTPUT") || !setup.includes("start_harbor_setup_inner")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install]
- label: Harbor App native setup smoke mode only exits successfully when the final setup detail status is ready
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); const start=src.indexOf("pub fn spawn_setup_smoke"); const body=src.slice(start); if (!body.includes("detail.status == \"ready\"") || !body.includes("ok: ready") || !body.includes("if ready { 0 } else { 1 }")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install]

## setup
- label: Harbor App exposes a centralized setup gate backed by typed Tauri setup commands before Harbor-dependent providers mount
  command: rg -q 'detect_harbor_setup|start_harbor_setup|cancel_harbor_setup|verify_harbor_cli|configure_first_run_stack|start_first_run_stack|verify_first_run_stack|open_webui' app/src-tauri/src && rg -q 'HarborSetupProvider' app/src
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup installs the CLI through the official install.sh path and setup logs include structured Harbor setup stage markers
  command: rg -q 'raw.githubusercontent.com/av/harbor/refs/heads/main/install.sh' app/src-tauri/src install.sh && rg -q 'HARBOR_SETUP_STAGE' install.sh requirements.sh
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup pulls the first-run llama.cpp smoke model through 'harbor models pull --source llamacpp' instead of the service-oriented 'harbor pull --source' path
  command: grep -Fq 'harbor_script(&["models", "pull", "--source", "llamacpp", FIRST_RUN_MODEL])' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && ! grep -Fq 'harbor_script(&["pull", "--source", "llamacpp", FIRST_RUN_MODEL])' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows setup runs Harbor detection, verification, first-run stack, and Open WebUI commands through a shared WSL bash helper that honors HARBOR_WSL_DISTRO
  command: rg -q 'wsl_bash_args|HARBOR_WSL_DISTRO' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'run_logged_wsl_bash' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: install.ps1 and the Tauri setup backend both expose local script override hooks so app installer paths can be exercised before publishing to main
  command: rg -q 'HARBOR_APP_INSTALL_SCRIPT' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'HARBOR_APP_WINDOWS_INSTALL_SCRIPT' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'HARBOR_INSTALL_SOURCE_PATH' install.sh install.ps1 tests/suites/01-install.sh
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows setup quotes PowerShell installer commands with PowerShell escaping instead of POSIX shell escaping
  command: rg -q 'powershell_quote' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'HARBOR_APP_WINDOWS_INSTALL_SCRIPT' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup parses HARBOR_SETUP_STAGE markers from installer stdout and stderr into live setup status events instead of treating them as plain log text
  command: rg -q 'parse_setup_stage_marker|HARBOR_SETUP_STAGE=' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'emit_stage\(.*marker' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup preserves installer refresh-required and blocked statuses when an installer exits non-zero after emitting those stage markers
  command: rg -q 'setup_status_from_error|HARBOR_SETUP_STATUS=' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: install.sh emits refresh-required when post-install harbor doctor indicates Docker group membership or session refresh is needed
  command: rg -q 'doctor_requires_refresh|refresh-required' install.sh && rg -q 'Docker.*group|newgrp docker|re-login' install.sh
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows setup discovers the preferred WSL2 Ubuntu distro in the Tauri backend and passes that same distro into install.ps1 and every WSL Harbor command
  command: rg -q 'preferred_wsl_distro|windows_install_script.*distro|wsl_bash_args' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q -- '-Distro' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup persists setup detail, current status, logs, and last error in localStorage so a remount or restart can resume with the previous setup context
  command: rg -q 'SETUP_STORAGE_KEY|readStoredSetupSnapshot|writeStoredSetupSnapshot' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx && rg -q 'localStorage' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: install.ps1 normalizes NUL-padded WSL list output before parsing distro names so Windows setup can select or validate the intended WSL2 Ubuntu distro
  command: rg -q 'function Normalize-WslOutput' install.ps1 && rg -Fq '$Text -replace' install.ps1 && rg -Fq '$distros = Normalize-WslOutput' install.ps1
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: requirements.sh macOS setup installs missing Homebrew through the official Homebrew installer and uses the Homebrew Docker Desktop cask when Docker is missing
  command: rg -q 'HOMEBREW_INSTALL_URL|install_homebrew|load_homebrew_shellenv' requirements.sh && rg -q 'brew install --cask docker' requirements.sh
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup screen shows a copyable manual installer command for advanced recovery on Linux, macOS, and Windows
  command: rg -q 'manualSetupCommand|IconCopy|navigator.clipboard.writeText' app/src/setup/HarborSetupGate.tsx
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: install.sh emits a blocked setup stage when post-install harbor doctor reports Docker daemon or Docker Desktop is not running or reachable
  command: rg -q 'doctor_requires_blocked|Docker daemon is not running|Please start Docker|setup_stage "blocked"' install.sh
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup maps first-run stack configuration, startup, and inference command failures to stage-specific remediation kinds instead of a generic setup failure
  command: rg -q 'remediationKindFromError|stack-config-failed|stack-start-failed|llamacpp-inference-failed' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows setup persists the selected WSL distro in app-local setup state and reuses it only while it still exists as a WSL2 distro
  command: rg -q 'stored_wsl_distro_path|read_stored_wsl_distro|persist_wsl_distro' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'parse_wsl_distro_exists' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup cancellation is tracked in the Tauri backend so a killed installer reports cancelled instead of being overwritten as a generic failed process
  command: rg -q 'cancel_requested|HARBOR_SETUP_STATUS=cancelled|cancelled;.*cancelled' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: install.ps1 uses a local Harbor source override by converting the host path to the WSL path and invoking that repo's install.sh with local source and requirements arguments
  command: grep -Fq 'wslpath -a' install.ps1 && grep -Fq -- '--source-path' install.ps1 && grep -Fq -- '--requirements-path' install.ps1 && grep -Fq 'install.sh' install.ps1
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App normalizes persisted setup snapshots so missing fields from older setup state are restored from the checking defaults before rendering
  command: rg -q 'normalizeSetupDetail' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx && rg -q '\.\.\.CHECKING_DETAIL, \.\.\.detail' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx && rg -q 'appVersion' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App missing-command detection compares process output case-insensitively across stdout and stderr before classifying Docker CLI as missing
  command: rg -q 'to_lowercase|to_ascii_lowercase' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'combined_output' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'Docker CLI is not installed' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup detection stops after a non-zero harbor doctor result and reports a verifying-cli remediation instead of continuing into first-run stack detection
  command: rg -q 'fn detect_doctor\(detail: &mut HarborSetupDetail\) -> bool' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'verification-failed' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q '!detect_doctor\(&mut detail\)' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup status events mark detail.running false for terminal statuses so ready, blocked, refresh-required, failed, and cancelled snapshots cannot remain running
  command: rg -q 'isTerminalSetupStatus' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx && rg -q 'ready.*blocked.*failed.*cancelled|refresh-required' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx && rg -q 'running: !isTerminalSetupStatus' app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: install.ps1 checks WSL availability through an explicit wsl.exe --status exit-code helper before selecting or installing a WSL distro
  command: rg -q 'function Test-WslAvailable' install.ps1 && rg -Fq '$LASTEXITCODE -eq 0' install.ps1 && rg -q 'if \(-not \(Test-WslAvailable\)\)' install.ps1
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Settings repair setup action uses the shared stage-aware setup action instead of always rerunning the full installer
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const ctx=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx","utf8"); const settings=fs.readFileSync("app/src/settings/Settings.tsx","utf8"); if (!ctx.includes("runRecommendedSetupAction") || !ctx.includes("status === \"blocked\"") || !ctx.includes("status === \"refresh-required\"") || !ctx.includes("startFirstRunStack")) process.exit(1); if (!settings.includes("onClick={setup.runRecommendedSetupAction}")) process.exit(1); if (settings.includes("onClick={setup.startSetup}")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows WSL Harbor commands shell-quote argv arguments before passing them through bash -lic
  command: test -f app/src/harborCommand.ts && rg -q buildWindowsHarborCommand app/src/harborCommand.ts app/src/useHarbor.tsx app/src/cli/CommandRunner.tsx app/src/terminal/harborPty.ts && rg -q shellQuote app/src/harborCommand.ts
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows post-setup Harbor command paths reuse the backend-selected WSL distro by passing -d before bash -lic
  command: rg -q 'get_harbor_wsl_distro' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs app/src-tauri/src/lib.rs app/src/harborCommand.ts && rg -q 'buildWindowsWslHarborArgs' app/src/harborCommand.ts app/src/useHarbor.tsx app/src/cli/CommandRunner.tsx app/src/terminal/harborPty.ts && rg -q 'args.push\("-d"' app/src/harborCommand.ts
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows terminal panel opens the backend-selected WSL distro instead of the WSL default distro
  command: rg -q 'buildWindowsWslArgs' app/src/terminal/TerminalPanel.tsx app/src/harborCommand.ts && rg -Fq 'buildWindowsWslArgs(["bash", "-l"])' app/src/terminal/TerminalPanel.tsx && ! rg -q 'const args: string\[\] = \[\]' app/src/terminal/TerminalPanel.tsx
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App first-run verification checks the rendered Open WebUI config contains the llama.cpp OpenAI backend URL
  command: rg -q 'verify_webui_llamacpp_config' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'http://llamacpp:8080/v1' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs services/webui/configs/config.llamacpp.json && rg -q 'webui-backend-config-failed' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App blocked Docker daemon remediation runs the setup repair path instead of only redetecting so install scripts can start or repair Docker
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx","utf8"); if (!src.includes("remediationKind === \"docker-daemon-unreachable\"")) process.exit(1); if (!/status === \"blocked\"[\s\S]*docker-daemon-unreachable[\s\S]*return startSetup\(\)/.test(src)) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: install.ps1 waits for Docker Desktop to become reachable inside the selected WSL distro after starting it before reporting WSL integration blocked
  command: rg -q 'Wait-WslDockerReady' install.ps1 && rg -q 'Start-DockerDesktop' install.ps1 && rg -q 'Start-Sleep -Seconds' install.ps1 && rg -q 'Docker Desktop did not become reachable inside WSL distro' install.ps1
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: requirements.sh starts Docker Desktop on macOS and waits for docker info when the Docker daemon is stopped
  command: rg -q 'start_macos_docker_desktop' requirements.sh && rg -q 'wait_for_docker_access' requirements.sh && rg -q 'open -g -a Docker' requirements.sh && rg -q 'Waiting for Docker daemon' requirements.sh
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App labels blocked Docker daemon remediation as a Docker setup repair action
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupGate.tsx","utf8"); if (!src.includes("remediationKind === \"docker-daemon-unreachable\"")) process.exit(1); if (!src.includes("Repair Docker setup")) process.exit(1); if (!src.includes("setupActionLabel(status, detail?.remediationKind)")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup backend includes the last PTY output line when a terminal setup marker causes a process failure so UI remediation can classify the real blocker
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!src.includes("last_line_state") || !src.includes("last_output_line")) process.exit(1); if (!src.includes("HARBOR_SETUP_STATUS={marker}") || !src.includes("{detail}")) process.exit(1); if (!src.includes("parse_setup_stage_marker(line)")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup remediation classification recognizes blocked Docker Desktop and WSL integration installer messages from preserved terminal output
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx","utf8"); if (!src.includes("Docker Desktop did not become reachable")) process.exit(1); if (!src.includes("Docker is not reachable")) process.exit(1); if (!src.includes("Start Docker Desktop")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App recommended setup action resumes starting-first-run-stack with the first-run stack flow instead of rerunning the full installer
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const ctx=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx","utf8"); const gate=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupGate.tsx","utf8"); if (!ctx.includes("status === \"starting-first-run-stack\"")) process.exit(1); if (!/status === \"configuring-first-run-stack\"[\s\S]*status === \"starting-first-run-stack\"[\s\S]*status === \"verifying-inference\"[\s\S]*return startFirstRunStack\(\)/.test(ctx)) process.exit(1); if (!gate.includes("status === \"starting-first-run-stack\"") || !gate.includes("Start first-run stack")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App first-run detection performs service health probes in the setup target, using WSL curl on Windows instead of host curl
  command: rg -q 'fn target_curl_url' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -q 'run_wsl_bash_timeout' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && rg -Fq 'shell_quote(url)' app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs && node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); const helperStart=src.indexOf("fn target_curl_url"); const helperEnd=src.indexOf("fn detect_first_run_stack", helperStart); const helper=src.slice(helperStart, helperEnd); if (!helper.includes("run_wsl_bash_timeout") || !helper.includes("shell_quote(url)")) process.exit(1); const start=src.indexOf("fn detect_first_run_stack"); const end=src.indexOf("#[tauri::command]", start); if (start < 0 || end < 0) process.exit(1); const body=src.slice(start,end); if (body.includes("run_capture(\"curl\"")) process.exit(1); if (!body.includes("target_curl_url")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App Windows setup detection classifies missing WSL or missing WSL2 Ubuntu as a prerequisite remediation before probing the Harbor CLI inside WSL
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!src.includes("fn detect_windows_target")) process.exit(1); const fnStart=src.indexOf("fn detect_windows_target"); const fnEnd=src.indexOf("fn detect_platform_blocker", fnStart); const body=src.slice(fnStart, fnEnd); if (!body.includes("wsl.exe") || !body.includes("--status") || !body.includes("--list") || !body.includes("--verbose")) process.exit(1); if (!body.includes("missing-wsl") || !body.includes("missing-wsl-distro") || !body.includes("checking-prerequisites")) process.exit(1); const detectStart=src.indexOf("pub fn detect_harbor_setup"); const detectEnd=src.indexOf("#[tauri::command]", detectStart + 1); const detectBody=src.slice(detectStart, detectEnd); for (const needle of ["detect_platform_blocker(&mut detail)", "detect_windows_target(&mut detail)", "!detect_cli(&mut detail)"]) if (!detectBody.includes(needle)) process.exit(1); if (!(detectBody.indexOf("detect_windows_target(&mut detail)") < detectBody.indexOf("!detect_cli(&mut detail)"))) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: requirements.sh macOS setup loads an existing Homebrew shellenv from standard install locations before running the Homebrew installer
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("requirements.sh","utf8"); const fnStart=src.indexOf("brew_install()"); const fnEnd=src.indexOf("ensure_linux_docker_service()", fnStart); const body=src.slice(fnStart, fnEnd); if (!body.includes("load_homebrew_shellenv")) process.exit(1); if (!/if ! load_homebrew_shellenv; then[\s\S]*install_homebrew/.test(body)) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App native post-setup Harbor command paths run through a fixed bash wrapper that includes ~/.local/bin and common package-manager bin directories so GUI-launched Linux and macOS apps can find the installed CLI
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const command=fs.readFileSync("app/src/harborCommand.ts","utf8"); const useHarbor=fs.readFileSync("app/src/useHarbor.tsx","utf8"); const runner=fs.readFileSync("app/src/cli/CommandRunner.tsx","utf8"); const pty=fs.readFileSync("app/src/terminal/harborPty.ts","utf8"); const caps=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/capabilities/default.json","utf8"); if (!command.includes("buildNativeHarborCommand") || !command.includes(".local/bin") || !command.includes("/opt/homebrew/bin") || !command.includes("/usr/local/bin") || !command.includes("export PATH=\"")) process.exit(1); if (!useHarbor.includes("Command.create(\"bash\", buildNativeHarborArgs(args))")) process.exit(1); if (!runner.includes("Command.create(\"bash\", buildNativeHarborArgs(args))")) process.exit(1); if (!pty.includes("spawn(\"bash\", buildNativeHarborArgs(args)")) process.exit(1); if (!caps.includes("\"name\": \"bash\"") || !caps.includes("\"cmd\": \"bash\"")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App native setup backend runs command probes with a standard GUI-safe PATH that includes ~/.local/bin, Homebrew, and common system bin directories
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!src.includes("fn native_command_path") || !src.includes(".local/bin") || !src.includes("/opt/homebrew/bin") || !src.includes("/usr/local/bin")) process.exit(1); const start=src.indexOf("fn run_capture"); const end=src.indexOf("fn run_shell", start); const body=src.slice(start,end); if (!body.includes("command.env(\"PATH\", path)") || !body.includes("platform_name() != \"windows\"")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App native setup detection checks the expected ~/.local/bin/harbor symlink and ~/.harbor/harbor.sh installation before reporting a missing CLI so a completed installer with a stale GUI PATH becomes refresh-required instead of generic missing-cli
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!src.includes("fn detect_native_harbor_install") || !src.includes(".local/bin/harbor") || !src.includes(".harbor/harbor.sh")) process.exit(1); const start=src.indexOf("fn detect_cli"); const end=src.indexOf("fn detect_docker", start); const body=src.slice(start,end); if (!body.includes("detect_native_harbor_install(detail)") || !body.includes("refresh-required") || !body.includes("cli-path-refresh")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App native post-setup Harbor command paths fall back to ~/.harbor/harbor.sh when the harbor symlink is absent so a valid official install remains usable after setup
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const command=fs.readFileSync("app/src/harborCommand.ts","utf8"); const setup=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!command.includes("function harbor()") || !command.includes("$HOME/.harbor/harbor.sh") || !command.includes("command -v harbor")) process.exit(1); if (!setup.includes("fn native_harbor_shell") || !setup.includes("function harbor()") || !setup.includes("$HOME/.harbor/harbor.sh")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup preserves failed terminal setup statuses after installer or stack process errors instead of immediately redetecting and overwriting the failure details
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx","utf8"); const start=src.indexOf("function shouldPreserveErrorStatus"); const end=src.indexOf("function isTerminalSetupStatus", start); const body=src.slice(start,end); if (!body.includes("status === \"failed\"")) process.exit(1); if (!body.includes("status === \"blocked\"") || !body.includes("status === \"refresh-required\"")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup retry action routes failed first-run stack remediations back to the first-run stack flow instead of rerunning full Harbor CLI installation
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const ctx=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx","utf8"); const gate=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupGate.tsx","utf8"); if (!ctx.includes("isFirstRunStackRemediation") || !ctx.includes("return startFirstRunStack()")) process.exit(1); if (!gate.includes("isFirstRunStackRemediation") || !gate.includes("Start first-run stack")) process.exit(1); if (!ctx.includes("stack-config-failed") || !ctx.includes("stack-start-failed") || !ctx.includes("llamacpp-inference-failed")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup timed command capture drains stdout and stderr while the child is still running so verbose detection commands cannot deadlock on full pipes and report false timeouts
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!src.includes("fn spawn_output_reader") || !src.includes("read_to_string") || !src.includes("stdout_reader") || !src.includes("stderr_reader")) process.exit(1); const start=src.indexOf("fn run_capture_timeout"); const end=src.indexOf("fn run_shell", start); const body=src.slice(start,end); if (!body.includes("spawn_output_reader") || !body.includes("reader.join().ok()") || !body.includes("child.kill()") || !body.includes("child.wait()")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup classifies first-run service readiness timeouts as stack-start-failed rather than llama.cpp inference failures so retry messaging points at stack startup
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const ctx=fs.readFileSync("app/src/setup/HarborSetupContext.tsx","utf8"); const setup=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!ctx.includes("Services did not start") || !ctx.includes("stack-start-failed")) process.exit(1); const start=ctx.indexOf("function remediationKindFromError"); const end=ctx.indexOf("export function isFirstRunStackRemediation", start); const body=ctx.slice(start,end); if (!(body.indexOf("Services did not start") < body.indexOf("verifying-inference"))) process.exit(1); if (!setup.includes("Services did not start within the expected time (stack-start-failed)")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup detection classifies first-run Open WebUI or llama.cpp service health failures as stack-start-failed instead of llama.cpp inference failures because inference has not run yet
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); const start=src.indexOf("if !webui_ok || !llamacpp_ok"); const end=src.indexOf("let webui_backend", start); if (start < 0 || end < 0) process.exit(1); const body=src.slice(start,end); if (!body.includes("stack-start-failed")) process.exit(1); if (body.includes("llamacpp-inference-failed")) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor App setup detection reports setup as running while the setup-wide active lock is held, even between child processes, so redetect cannot overwrite an in-progress install or first-run stack chain
  command: node -e 'const fs=require("fs"); const src=fs.readFileSync("app/src-tauri/src/setup.rs","utf8"); if (!src.includes("fn setup_is_active") || !src.includes("setup_active")) process.exit(1); const start=src.indexOf("pub fn detect_harbor_setup"); const end=src.indexOf("#[tauri::command]", start + 1); const body=src.slice(start,end); if (!body.includes("setup_is_active(&state)") || !/let running =[\s\S]*child_running[\s\S]*\|\|[\s\S]*setup_is_active\(&state\)/.test(body)) process.exit(1);'
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]

# boost
- label: Boost is an LLM proxy built with Python/FastAPI that transforms chat completions via pluggable modules
  command: grep -q 'fastapi' services/boost/pyproject.toml

## modules
- label: Boost modules are Python files exporting ID_PREFIX and an async apply(chat, llm) function
  command: grep -rq 'ID_PREFIX' services/boost/src/modules/ && grep -rq 'async def apply' services/boost/src/modules/
- label: Boost has 19 built-in modules and 25+ custom modules
  command: test $(find services/boost/src/modules -name '*.py' ! -name '__*' | wc -l) -ge 19 && test $(find services/boost/src/custom_modules -name '*.py' ! -name '__*' | wc -l) -ge 25
- label: Boost modules are loaded dynamically from modules/ and custom_modules/ directories via importlib
  command: grep -q 'importlib' services/boost/src/mods.py

## api
- label: Boost exposes OpenAI-compatible endpoints: /v1/models and /v1/chat/completions
  command: grep -q '/v1/models' services/boost/src/main.py && grep -q '/v1/chat/completions' services/boost/src/main.py
- label: Boost supports SSE streaming and WebSocket event delivery
  command: grep -q 'WebSocket' services/boost/src/main.py && grep -q 'EventSourceResponse\|StreamingResponse' services/boost/src/main.py
- label: Boost CORS is enabled for all origins
  command: grep -q 'allow_origins' services/boost/src/main.py
- label: Boost streaming chat completions emit an OpenAI-compatible terminal chunk with a non-null finish_reason before data: [DONE] so strict clients such as Pi can finish streams correctly
  command: rg -q 'finish_reason="stop"' services/boost/src/llm.py && rg -q 'test_emit_done_adds_terminal_chunk_before_done' services/boost/tests/test_streaming.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost /v1/models endpoint auto-detects response format based on client headers, returning Anthropic ModelInfo format for Anthropic SDK clients and OpenAI format otherwise
  command: grep -q '_is_anthropic_client' services/boost/src/main.py && grep -q '_to_anthropic_model' services/boost/src/main.py && grep -q 'model_id' services/boost/src/main.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost /v1/chat/completions endpoint remains fully functional after compat layer additions, verified by dedicated regression test suite covering streaming, non-streaming, auth, validation, and BackendError handling
  command: test -f services/boost/tests/test_chat_completions.py && rg -q 'v1/chat/completions' services/boost/tests/test_chat_completions.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost full-app Responses and Anthropic compatibility routes preserve SDK request ID headers on stub and auth-error responses
  command: python -m pytest services/boost/tests/test_endpoint_isolation.py::TestFullAppSdkRequestIdHeaders -q
  tags: [spec, boost-full-app-sdk-request-ids, implemented]
- label: Boost /v1/models returns SDK-specific request ID headers on list, lookup, and not-found responses for both OpenAI and Anthropic clients
  command: python -m pytest services/boost/tests/test_models.py::TestModelRequestIdHeaders -q
  tags: [spec, boost-models-sdk-request-ids, implemented]
- Boost mapper.py deeper branches for HTTP chat/tool paths (list_downstream 20-59 http/except/minimax-register, resolve_proxy_model/module/workflow 74-98 ifs, resolve_request_config ValueError 106 + HTTP 404 118 + tools params keep 104, is_direct_task 158) must be driven real via /v1/models + /v1/chat/completions (with tools payloads) in test_config.py only (non-prior file for deeper mapper, no repeat iter10 chat test); using real import/rebind + httpx patch for success list + config for minimax/errors + LLM patch for early return, asserting responses and mapper branches @implemented
- Boost main.py remaining HTTP handler paths in chat/models (210 x-api-key branch in _is_anthropic_client, 278-289/335-346 model list/by-id 5xx error envelopes for anthro/openai via _is detection, 298-310 404 not-found shaped responses, 323/ openai returns, 415-436 chat serve() + if-None + stream/else + BackendError handler that forwards headers) must be driven to coverage exclusively via real HTTP TestClient calls using the mandated safe general test_config.py (_make_fresh_app reloads + header variants for anthro detection + patches on mapper/llm to force excepts + non-direct serve + BackendError raise); new tests appended in dedicated Test class following existing patterns, no other test files or priors touched @implemented
- Boost HTTP handlers in main.py (esp /v1/chat/completions) must cover plain non-HTTPException 500 error paths (e.g. UnicodeDecodeError from body.decode('utf-8') not caught by the narrow JSONDecodeError except, or uncaught Exception from list_downstream/LLM/serve outside BackendError catch) which yield the default FastAPI/Starlette plain-text 500 'Internal Server Error' (text/plain, no JSON envelope from the HTTPException-only handler); exercised exclusively via TestClient calls (with bad bytes content= or side-effect patches raising non-BE) in the safe general test_config.py only (using _make_fresh_app + raise_server_exceptions=False + asserts on status/text/content-type NOT json-shaped); new TestPlainNonHTTP5xxPaths class appended, no other test files or priors touched @implemented

## anthropic compat
- label: Boost exposes POST /v1/messages endpoint for Anthropic Messages API compatibility
  command: rg -q '/v1/messages' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'anthropic_compatible_routes' services/boost/src/main.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost exposes POST /v1/messages/count_tokens endpoint for Anthropic token counting
  command: rg -q 'count_tokens' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'input_tokens' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat converts incoming Anthropic messages to OpenAI format internally via _convert_messages
  command: rg -q '_convert_messages' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q '_convert_user_message' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q '_convert_assistant_message' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat streaming converts OpenAI SSE chunks to Anthropic SSE events (message_start, content_block_start, content_block_delta, content_block_stop, message_delta, message_stop)
  command: rg -q 'message_start' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'content_block_start' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'content_block_delta' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'content_block_stop' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'message_delta' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'message_stop' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat accepts x-api-key header for authentication alongside standard Authorization header
  command: rg -q 'x-api-key' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q '_synthesize_authorization' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: HARBOR_BOOST_ANTHROPIC_COMPAT config controls whether Anthropic-compatible endpoints are registered
  command: rg -q 'ENABLE_ANTHROPIC_COMPAT' services/boost/src/config.py && rg -q 'HARBOR_BOOST_ANTHROPIC_COMPAT' profiles/default.env && rg -q 'ENABLE_ANTHROPIC_COMPAT' services/boost/src/main.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat maps stop reasons between formats (length->max_tokens, tool_calls->tool_use, stop->end_turn)
  command: rg -q '_map_stop_reason' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'max_tokens' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'end_turn' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'tool_use' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat converts tool schemas between Anthropic and OpenAI formats
  command: rg -q '_convert_tools' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q '_convert_tool_choice' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'input_schema' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat includes request-id header in all response paths
  command: rg -q 'REQUEST_ID_HEADER' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'request-id' services/boost/src/compat_utils.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat handles mid-stream errors gracefully with proper SSE envelope closure
  command: rg -q 'except.*Exception' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'test_mid_stream_exception' services/boost/tests/test_anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat supports extended thinking by mapping thinking param to max_completion_tokens, producing thinking content blocks from backend reasoning_content, and stripping thinking blocks from request message history
  command: rg -q 'thinking' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'reasoning_content' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'thinking_delta' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'test_assistant_message_thinking_blocks_stripped' services/boost/tests/test_anthropic_compat.py && rg -q 'test_reasoning_content_produces_thinking_block' services/boost/tests/test_anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat passes through top_k parameter for backends that support it (vLLM, Ollama, llama.cpp)
  command: grep -q 'top_k' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'test_top_k' services/boost/tests/test_anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat accepts the anthropic-beta request header with comma-separated feature flags, logs them at debug level, and echoes recognized flags back in the anthropic-beta response header
  command: grep -q '_parse_beta_flags' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'RECOGNIZED_BETA_FLAGS' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'anthropic-beta.*join' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat supports document content blocks with best-effort conversion (image types forwarded as images, others as text placeholders) and URL image sources
  command: grep -q 'document' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'source_type == "url"' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic streaming emits a ping event after message_start for connection keepalive
  command: grep -q 'ping' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'TestStreamingPingEvent' services/boost/tests/test_anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat returns anthropic-version response header on all response paths
  command: grep -q 'ANTHROPIC_VERSION_HEADER' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'ANTHROPIC_VERSION' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
  tags: [spec, implemented]
- label: Boost Anthropic compat correctly distinguishes stop_sequence vs end_turn stop reasons by matching response content against configured stop_sequences
  command: grep -q 'stop_sequence' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'end_turn' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py && grep -q 'content_text' services/boost/src/anthropic_compat.py
