# dev

## lint
- label: Harbor lint implementation files and fixtures live under .scripts/lint, not scripts/lint
  command: test -f .scripts/lint/run.ts && test -f .scripts/lint/self-test.ts && test -f .scripts/lint/rules.yaml && test ! -e scripts/lint
  tags: [spec, lint-migration, implemented]
- label: The repository does not unignore scripts/lint because scripts/ is reserved for local gitignored files
  command: grep -q '^scripts/\*$' .gitignore && ! grep -q '^!scripts/lint/' .gitignore
  tags: [spec, lint-migration, implemented]
- label: harbor dev lint and harbor dev lint-self-test dispatch directly to .scripts/lint implementations
  command: grep -q './lint/run.ts' .scripts/lint.ts && grep -q './lint/self-test.ts' .scripts/lint-self-test.ts && ! grep -R -q '../scripts/lint' .scripts/lint.ts .scripts/lint-self-test.ts
  tags: [spec, lint-migration, implemented]

# tests

## app-install
- label: The integration VM install suite runs the programmatic app installer path and verifies first-run Open WebUI plus llama.cpp commands are wired
  command: rg -q 'HARBOR_INSTALL_SOURCE_PATH' tests/suites/01-install.sh && rg -q 'install.sh' tests/suites/01-install.sh && rg -q 'harbor up --no-defaults llamacpp webui' tests/suites/01-install.sh && rg -q 'models.*pull.*--source.*llamacpp' tests/suites/01-install.sh
  tags: [spec, app-install, implemented]
- label: Harbor native setup integration spec documents verifiable Linux macOS and Windows first-run setup tests with host prerequisites and machine-checkable expectations
  command: test -f tests/app-native-setup.md && rg -q '## Prerequisites' tests/app-native-setup.md && rg -q 'macOS Ready Path' tests/app-native-setup.md && rg -q 'Windows Ready Path' tests/app-native-setup.md && rg -q 'HARBOR_APP_SETUP_SMOKE_OUTPUT' tests/app-native-setup.md
  tags: [spec, app-install]
